xiaolin zheng group stanford skip navigation stanford university zheng research group z home research people publications news positions research topics welcome our lab studies the interfacial science among thermofluidics chemistry and nanomaterials specifically we are developing simple and low cost flame synthesis method to grow one dimensional nanowires and applying these nanowires in energy conversion combustion and propulsion and chemical and biological sensing systems to exploit their unique properties representative research topics are listed below nanowire based flame synthesis of nanomaterials nanostructured energy conversion systems nanoelectronics stanford university stanford me stanford thermosciences the wiki last updated feb 20th 2012
